<h3>Perception Skills:</h3>
<div>
    <h4>Aircraft Pilot</h4>
    <p>A pilot must use this skill while in atmospheric flight to navigate around obstacles, land in difficult situations, and dodge enemy fire.  Aircraft Pilot is also used in atmosphere to hold a tail on an enemy fighter or to break away from a fighter who is tailing. See Dogfighting for more advanced tools for Aircraft Pilots:</p>
    <p>Complexity: Complexity is used against the aircraft being flown.  It can also be added to non opposed flight checks. (Such as landing or obstacles)</p>
    <p>
        Specializations: A specialization can be chosen off of a favored aircraft type
        (Fighter, Scout, Heavy Fighter, Transport, Heavy Transport, Corvette etc…); specializing in this type of aircraft gives a +1 to all Aircraft Pilot rolls when using that type of aircraft.
    </p>
</div>

<div>
    <h4>Investigation</h4>
    <p>Investigation is used during searches for obscure details.  Investigation may be applied when searching a room for a blood sample, reviewing security footage for hidden details, or even looking through a large catalogue for a piece of information.</p>
    <p>Complexity: Complexity is set by the target being investigated, a default of 1 is set as the basic Investigation difficulty.</p>
    <h5>Specializations:</h5>
    <dl>
        <dt>Thorough Investigator</dt>
        <dd>Automatically succeeds on Investigation checks as long as the investigator spends time investigating equal to (complexity of the check*1 hour).</dd>
        <dt>Deductive</dt>
        <dd>The player can use their Investigation complexity in place of their Human Perception complexity when making Human Perception checks.</dd>
    </dl>
</div>

<div>
    <h4>Combat Sense</h4>
    <p>Combat sense determines the reactions of individuals during the high stress environment of combat.  Combat Sense is rolled in the beginning of every combat, The individuals then act in their perspective combat sense order from highest to lowest. Ties in combat sense order are broken by Complexity first, then perception.</p>
    <p>Complexity: Complexity is used to adjust to certain equipment that may be worn that may hamper response time.  Night Vision (CPX 2)   Thermal (CPX 3)  Sonar (CPX 4).</p>
    <h5>Specializations:</h5>
    <dl>
        <dt>Reactive Retina</dt>
        <dd>Changing optics is a free action instead of a quick action.</dd>
        <dt>Point Man</dt>
        <dd>+1 to CS on first round of combat.</dd>
        <dt>Battle Buddy</dt>
        <dd>Quick action, pick an ally within 10 meters, they gain +1 CS.</dd>
        <dt>Hyper Combative</dt>
        <dd>Grants the ability to remove skill dice for individual +1 roll bonuses.</dd>
    </dl>
</div>

<div>
    <h4>Sniper <span>(Requirement 1/Small Arms)</span></h4>
    <p>Sniper is a skill that focuses on the ability to use rifles with precision at long ranges. In order for a character to use their sniper skill, they must not have moved this round.  Sniper must be used on a Rifle or designated “Sniper” weapon system, and can not fire this skill while utilizing more than a rate of fire of 0. The sniper skill can never be used to suppress enemies, or skills that use suppression like effects. Characters who aim with the sniper skill gain two aim dice for every round they aim, they may expand the number of aim dice they can use to twice their characters Sniper skill level.  These aim dice are forfeit if the Sniper uses any other skill (Including Defensive checks). Aim dice are spent when the weapon has fired.</p>
    <p>Complexity: Complexity is based off of the rifle used for the Sniper skill.</p>
    <h5>Specializations:</h5>
    <dl>
        <dt>Extended Shot</dt>
        <dd>The Sniper can shoot 1 bracket beyond maximum (X2 Max range) at an additional -2 (-6).</dd>
        <dt>Cover Reduction</dt>
        <dd>All shots ignore 1 cover bonus (This includes shooting through walls with a +3 cover)</dd>
        <dt>Fast Follow up</dt>
        <dd>Starts a new aim dice pool of 1 after a weapon is fired using the Sniper skill.</dd>
    </dl>
</div>

<div>
    <h4>Notice</h4>
    <p>The action of spotting out objects or actions quickly in an area.  Notice can involve any of the senses to locate a target object in an area.</p>
    <table>
        <caption>Notice Bonuses</caption>
        <tr>
            <td>Human</td>
            <td>Within 10 Meters (Close +1)</td>
