    <p>The Social Sciences skill judges a character's ability to recall knowledge pertaining to societal ethos, cultural phenomena, language groups, cultural xenology and related knowledge.</p>
    <p>
        Linguistics: The amount of languages known is equal to (1 + Knowledge + Social Science Complexity) to a minimum of 1.
        Archeology: This measures the ability to identify known ancient treasures or cultural links to found items of significance.
        History: Gives the capability to recall information about obscure history that will pertain to mission.
