    <h4>Diplomacy</h4>
    <p>The Diplomacy skill judges a character's ability to generate good will towards himself in a social setting. Diplomacy skill checks are typically rolled when asking for favors, displaying social etiquette or gaining a character’s trust, and are typically opposed by the Diplomacy or Human Perception of the character being interacted with. (Note: By its nature, Diplomacy is a particularly nonquantitative skill; therefore, MoS, MoF and its effects are largely subject to DM’s discretion)</p>
    <p>Complexity: The Complexity of Diplomacy sets the difficulty of the opposed check.</p>
    <p>Specializations: Diplomacy Specialization is generalist in nature, therefore, it will add a +1 each time a Diplomacy specialization is taken.</p>
